ef>\n* AIA New York Chapter, President - 1992<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://nyrej.com/aia-new-york-leads-the-charge-to-amend-aia-code-of-ethics|title=AIA New York leads the charge to amend AIA Code of Ethics|date=6 November 2018|work=New York Real Estate Journal|access-date=3 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":10\" /><ref name=\":13\" />\n* AIA New York Chapter Women in Architecture Leadership Network Founder - 1991<ref name=\":10\" />\n*[[New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission]], Commissioner - 1984-1987<ref name=\":8\" /><ref name=\":13\" />\n*[[New York State Council on the Arts]], Architecture Panel - 1980-1983<ref name=\":12\" />\n*[https://archleague.org The Architectural League of New York], (President 1985-1989) - 1975 - Present<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archleague.org/about/board-of-directors/|title=Board of Directors|last=|first=|date=|website=The Architectural League of New York|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Academic Appointments'''\n\n*[[University of Maryland, Baltimore|University of Maryland]], Kea Visiting Distinguished Professor - 2009<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arch.umd.edu/arch/kea-recipient/frances-halsband|title=Kea Professorship|last=|first=|date=2009|website=University of Maryland School of Architecture, Planning and Preservation|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n*[[University of Cincinnati]], Visiting Professor, Neihoff Studio - 2002<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bach|first=John|url=https://magazine.uc.edu/issues/1107/power.html|title=The Power of Place: Measuring the human impact of UC's architectural renaissance|date=November 2007|work=University of Cincinnati Magazine|access-date=3 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign|University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign]], Plym Professor - 2001<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://arch.illinois.edu/engagement/plym-distinguished-professors|titl