 de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]])<ref name=\"Spain\">{{cite web|url=http://spanishcharts.com/weekchart.asp?cat=s3&year=2018&date=20180128|title=Spain Digital & Physical Songs Sales|publisher=spanishcharts.com|date=28 January 2018|accessdate=14 March 2018}}</ref>\n| 9\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Sweden Digital Songs (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref name=\"Sweden\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2018-01-27/sweden-digital-song-sales|title=Sweden Digital Song Sales|work=Billboard|date=27 January 2018|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n| 5\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|38|date=20180413|rowheader=true|accessdate=14 April 2018|refname=\"ukchart\"}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UKdownload|11|date=20180302|rowheader=true|accessdate=3 April 2019|refname=\"ukDownload\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UKindie|5|date=20180126|rowheader=true|accessdate=27 January 2018|refname=\"ukindie\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboarddanceclubplay|1|artist=Kylie Minogue|rowheader=true|accessdate=4 May 2018|refname=\"DanceClubSongs\"}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US Hot Dance Club Songs (''Billboard'')<ref>http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2018/dance-club-songs</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|37\n|-\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Australia|award=Gold|artist=Kylie Minogue|title=Dancing|type=single|access-date=10 July 2018|certyear=2018|refname=aria_cert}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|nocert=true|title=Dancing|artist=Kylie Minogue|type=single|salesamount=64,609|salesref=<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/the-opening-week-is-a-real-statement-kylie-minogue-hits-no-1-with-bmg/072121|title='The opening week is a real statement': Kylie Minogue hits No.1 with BMG|last=Paine|first=Andre|date=April 13, 2018|work=[[Music Week]]|access-date=August 26, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707063738/http://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/the-opening-week-is-a-real-statement-kylie-minogue-hits-no-1-with-bmg/072121|archivedate=July 7, 2018}}</ref>|access-date=}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 19 January 2018\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| Darenote\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/hear-kylie-minogues-euphoric-new-song-dancing-w515625|title=Hear Kylie Minogue's Euphoric New Song 'Dancing' Off New LP 'Golden'|publisher=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=19 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia\n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| {{hlist|Liberator|[[BMG Rights Management|BMG]]}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://themusicnetwork.com/news/most-added-kylie-was-and-always-will-be-radios-treasure|title=Most Added: Kylie was, and always will, be radio's treasure|publisher=The Music Network|date=25 January 2018|accessdate=25 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Italy\n| rowspan=\"2\"| BMG\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://radiodate.it/radio-date/kylie-minogue-dancing-177299-19-01-2018-radiodate/|title=Kylie Minogue - Dancing RadioDate|publisher=Radio Airplay FM|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=19 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United Kingdom\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09lt16j|title=Kylie Minogue World Exclusive and Winnie the Pooh|publisher=[[BBC Radio 2]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=25 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\"| Various\n| 23 February 2018\n| {{hlist|Digital download|streaming}} (Initial Talk remix)\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Darenote\n| <ref name=\"initial\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/50eFKER8Q5s0q3LP7oeklx|title=Dancing (Initial Talk Remix)|publisher=[[Spotify]]|accessdate=9 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2 March 2018\n| {{hlist|Digital download|streaming}} ([[Illyus & Barrientos]] remix)\n| <ref name=\"illyus\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/1tdVedvLnQ7GCAIECfqSEF\n|title=Dancing (Illyus & Barrientos Remix)|publisher=Spotify|accessdate=9 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 9 March 2018\n| {{hlist|Digital download|streaming}} ([[Anton Powers]] remix)\n| <ref name=\"anton\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/track/2SyYwbZiatwvdhKDBU4Hzh|title=Dancing - Anton Powers Remix|publisher=Spotify|accessdate=9 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Germany\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 6 April 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Gramophone record|Vinyl]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| BMG\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jpc.de/jpcng/poprock/detail/-/art/kylie-minogue-dancing/hnum/8111258|language=German|title= Kylie Minogue: Dancing (Single 7\")|publisher=[[jpc (retailer)|JPC]]|accessdate=9 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| <ref name=\"vinyl\"/>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of number-one dance singles of 2018 (U.S.)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kylie Minogue songs}}\n\n[[Category:2018 singles]]\n[[Category:2018 songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Kylie Minogue songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Kylie Minogue]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Steve McEwan]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Nathan Chapman (record producer)]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Sophie Muller]]\n[[Category:Songs about death]]\n[[Category:Songs about dancing]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Dancing\n| cover      = Kylie Minogue - Dancing.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Kylie Minogue]]\n| album      = [[Golden (Kylie Minogue album)|Golden]]\n| B-side     = Rollin'\n| released   = 19 January 2018\n| format     =\n* [[CD single]]\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Gramophone record|vinyl]]\n| recorded   = 2017\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n* [[Electropop]]\n* [[country pop]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Bangers, Ballads & Bops: The 100 Best Singles Of 2018 |url=http://www.idolator.com/7690250/100-best-singles-of-2018?view-all |website=Idolator |accessdate=1 October 2019}}</ref>\n| length     = {{Duration|m=2|s=58}}\n| label      = [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]]\n| writer     =\n* Kylie Minogue\n* [[Steve McEwan]]\n* [[Nathan Chapman (record producer)|Nathan Chapman]]\n| producer   = Sky Adams\n| prev_title = [[Wonderful Christmastime#Kylie Minogue version|Wonderful Christmastime]]\n| prev_year  = 2016\n| next_title = [[Stop Me from Falling]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{Youtube|-BDImdAfodA|\"Dancing\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Dancing'''\" is a song by Australian singer [[Kylie Minogue]]. It was released on 19 January 2018 by [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]] and Liberator Music, as the lead single from her fourteenth studio album ''[[Golden (Kylie Minogue album)|Golden]]'' (2018). Written by Minogue, [[Steve McEwan]] and [[Nathan Chapman (record producer)|Nathan Chapman]], and produced by Sky Adams, \"Dancing\" was the singer's first material with BMG and Liberator, after finishing her contract with British label [[Parlophone]] two years prior. Musically, \"Dancing\" is a departure from her usual [[electronic dance music|electronic dance]] sound, and adapts to [[country pop]] with elements of [[electronica]] and [[dance-pop]]. Lyrically, it talks about having fun and enjoying life, with [[death]] and [[time]] being incorporated into the song's themes.\n\n\"Dancing\" received critical acclaim from [[music journalism|music critics]], many whom praised the song's production and lyrical quality. Upon its release on the parent album, certain critics had chosen it as a highlight. Commercially, the track reached the top twenty in regions such as Spain, Scotland, Hungary and Poland. It became the singer's 51st top-forty entry on the [[UK Singles Chart]], and her 14th number-one hit on the US [[Dance Club Songs]] chart. Additionally, despite staying one week in the Top 50 in her native Australia,<ref name=\"Australia\" /> \"Dancing\" was certified gold by the [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] for sales exceeding 35,000 units.\n\nDirected by [[Sophie Muller]], the music video features Minogue dancing and singing in several backdrops that were inspired by the [[Country music|Country and Western]] culture, such as the work of [[Dolly Parton]], and used motifs and imagery revolving around death. To promote the single, Minogue performed the song on her [[Kylie Presents Golden]] tour, and at several gigs and shows including ''[[Ant & Dec's Saturday Night Takeaway]]'', ''[[Sport Relief]]'', the [[Echo Music Prize]] in Germany, and when she headlined [[Radio 2 Live in Hyde Park]].\n\n==Background and composition==\nIn 2016, Minogue released her final studio album with long-term record label [[Parlophone]], entitled ''[[Kylie Christmas: Snow Queen Edition]]''.<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title=Kylie Christmas: Snow Queen Edition|others=Minogue, Kylie|date=2016|type=CD Album|publisher=[[Parlophone]]|id=0190295890728|location=United Kingdom}}</ref> After her departure from the label, Minogue signed a new record deal with [[BMG Rights Management]] which will release her upcoming album internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/kylie-minogue-signs-new-record-deal-with-bmg-new-album-expected-this-year__18062/|title=Kylie Minogue signs new record deal with BMG, new album expected this year|publisher=officialcharts.com|accessdate=1 February 2017}}</ref> In December 2017, Minogue and BMG had struck a joint-deal with [[Mushroom Group|Mushroom Music Labels]] \u2014 under the sub-division label Liberator Music to release her new album in Australia and New Zealand.<ref name=\"Mushroom Promotions 1\">{{cite news|title=Kylie Minogue {{!}} New Album Reunites Pop Princess With Mushroom Group In Australia {{!}} Mushroom Promotions|url=https://mushroompromotions.com/press-releases/kylie-minogue-new-album-reunites-pop-princess-mushroom-group-australia/|work=Mushroom Promotions|publisher=[[Mushroom Group]]|date=8 December 2017|accessdate=8 December 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208142226/https://mushroompromotions.com/press-releases/kylie-minogue-new-album-reunites-pop-princess-mushroom-group-australia/|archivedate=8 December 2017}}</ref> Throughout that year, Minogue worked with writers and producers for her fourteenth studio album including [[Amy Wadge]], Sky Adams, [[DJ Fresh]], [[Nathan Chapman (record producer)|Nathan Chapman]], and teamed with previous collaborators [[Biffco|Richard Stannard]], [[The Invisible Men]] and [[Karen Poole]].<ref name=\"lgbt\">{{cite web|author=Rudolph, Christopher|url=http://www.newnownext.com/kylie-minogue-new-album-lgbt-rights/06/2017/|title=Kylie Minogue's New Album Will Feature Songs About LGBT Rights|publisher=NewNowNext|date=6 June 2017|accessdate=19 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=White, Jack|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/kylie-minogue-has-hit-the-studio-with-dj-fresh-ahead-on-her-new-album__19869/|title=Kylie Minogue has hit the studio with DJ Fresh ahead on her new album|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=7 August 2017|accessdate=19 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"heraldsun\">{{cite web|author=Adams, Cameron|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/lifestyle/melbourne/first-review-kylies-new-single-dancing-is-country-meets-club/news-story/6e284ab9ec7c514f7d6db53837b2b195|title=First review: Kylie's new single Dancing is country meets club|work=[[Herald Sun]]|date=18 January 2018|accessdate=19 January 2018}}</ref> \"Dancing\" was one of the tracks written and recorded in [[Nashville]], [[Tennessee]], where she felt the location had a \"profound\" effect on her.<ref name=\"lgbt\"/> It was co-written by Minogue alongside Wadge and Adams, whereas production was solely handled by the latter artist. Minogue used [[Instagram]] to discuss the story of the single, saying that the track is about removing \"hurdles\" in life by \"dancing and having a good time\".<ref name=\"bbcradio\">{{cite web|author=Minogue, Kylie|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BeD0pQzn2r7/|title=I'm So Excited! Chris Evans will have the exclusive first play of my new single 'Dancing' on his BBC Radio 2 show tomorrow. Get those alarms set and tune in from 8am!|publisher=[[Instagram]]|date=18 January 2018|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n\"Dancing\" runs for two minutes and 58 seconds.<ref name=\"itunes\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/golden-deluxe-edition/1336301520|title=Golden (Deluxe Edition) by Kylie Minogue on Apple Music|publisher=iTunes Store (Australia) |accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref> Music critics have described the track as \"[[Country pop|country]]/[[electropop]]\".<ref name=\"Damshenas\"/><ref name=\"idolatormikewass\">{{cite web|author=Wass, Mike|url=https://www.idolator.com/7674338/kylie-minogue-dancing-video-preview|title=Kylie Minogue Teases Her Boot-Scootin' \"Dancing\" Video|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=30 January 2018|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', Daniel Kreps noted that Minogue's work in Nashville was \"evident\" to the single, exemplifying its \"acoustic guitar fingerpicking and Minogue brandishing some twang\" at the opening of the song.<ref name=\"rollingstone\">{{cite web|author=Kreps, Daniel|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/hear-kylie-minogues-euphoric-new-song-dancing-w515625|title=Hear Kylie Minogue's Euphoric New Song 'Dancing' Off New LP 'Golden'|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> Similarly, Nick Reilly from ''[[NME]]'' noticed Minogue's \"unlikely foray\" to Country music, but complimented the track's progression to the \"huge pop chorus\".<ref name=\"nme\">{{cite web|author=Reilly, Nick|url=http://www.nme.com/news/music/listen-dancing-comeback-single-kylie-minogue-2222053|title=Listen to 'Dancing', the comeback single from Kylie Minogue|work=[[NME]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> ''[[Vice (magazine)|Noisey]]'''s editor Lauren O'Neill found elements of [[electronic music]] in the song. Additionally, she compared the track's sound to the innovations of [[electronic dance music]] today\u2014alongside Minogue's previous experimentations\u2014and felt Minogue's offering was \"more successful\" than other \"popstars\".<ref name=\"noisey\">{{cite web|author=O'Neill, Lauren|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_uk/article/vbynqd/kylie-minogue-has-delivered-2018s-first-true-pop-banger-with-dancing|title=Kylie Minogue Has Delivered 2018's First True Pop Banger with \"Dancing\"|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Noisey]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> A contributor at ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' described it as a \"top 40 version of [[Young Thug]]'s country rap experiment \"You Said\"\", though they noted its more of a \"rootsy dance\" hybrid.<ref>{{cite web|author=Burks, Tosten|url=https://www.spin.com/2018/01/kylie-minogue-dancing-stream/|title=Kylie Minogue \u2013 \"Dancing\"|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> Minogue commented about the track's production and entire form in an interview with ''[[Herald Sun]]'' in Australia;\n{{blockquote|\"You've got the lyrical edge, that country feel, mixed with some sampling of the voice and electronic elements, so it does what it says on the label. And I love that it's called 'Dancing', it's immediately accessible and seemingly so obvious, but there's depth within the song\".<ref name=\"heraldsun\"/>}}\n\n==Release==\n\"Dancing\" was released on 19 January 2018 by [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]] and Liberator Music, as the lead single from her fourteenth studio album ''[[Golden (Kylie Minogue album)|Golden]]'' (2018).<ref name=\"goldendownload\">{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/dancing/1336206506?i=1336206687|title=Golden by Kylie Minogue|publisher=[[iTunes|iTunes UK]]|accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref> It also served as the singer's first material with BMG and Liberator, after finishing her contract with British label [[Parlophone]] two years prior. A [[Phonograph record|7\" vinyl]] was included in various package bundles on the singers website, promoting the release of the parent album; this included the B-side track \"Rollin'\", which appeared as a bonus track on deluxe editions of the album.<ref name=\"vinyl\">{{cite AV media notes|title=Dancing|others=Kylie Minogue|year=2018|type=7\" vinyl|publisher=Liberator Music|id=538360851, 4050538360851}}</ref> A limited edition [[CD single]] were distributed in Australia and New Zealand for the annual [[Mardi Gras]] Fair Day, which included the standard version of the album and a T-shirt.<ref name=\"cdsingle\">{{cite AV media notes|title=Dancing|others=Kylie Minogue|year=2018|type=CD single|publisher=Liberator Music|id=LIB215CD, 9341004057036}}</ref>\n\nThroughout February and March 2018, Minogue's company Darenote distributed digital remixes of \"Dancing\", featuring the work of Initial Talk, [[Illyus & Barrientos]], [[Anton Powers]] and Dimmi; Powers' version including both a radio and extended edit.<ref name=\"initial\"/><ref name=\"illyus\"/><ref name=\"anton\"/> Additionally, Minogue re-packaged the single releases of the first three artists into one format, and released it on her website.<ref name=\"websitedownload\">{{cite web |url=https://kylie.tmstor.es/cart/product.php?id=37103|title=Kylie \u2013 Dancing EP (Digital Download)|publisher=Kylie.com|accessdate=10 April 2018}}</ref> Dimmi's remix only premiered in France via [[iTunes]].<ref name=\"dimmi\">{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/fr/album/dancing-dimmi-remix-single/1384921236?l=en|title=Dancing (DIMMI remix) \u2013 Single|publisher=iTunes France|accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref> The cover art were re-colored versions of the standard picture, which was a promotional shot of Minogue during the ''Golden'' photoshoot.<ref name=\"cdsingle\"/>\n\n==Critical reception==\n[[File:Kylie Minogue - Golden Tour - Motorpoint Arena - Nottingham - 20.09.18. - ( 44 ) (44648057710).jpg|thumb|upright|Minogue performing \"Dancing\" as the final number of the [[Golden Tour]].]]\n\"Dancing\" received critical acclaim from [[Music journalism|music critics]]. Joey Nolfi from ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' called it a \"welcome return to form for the singer-songwriter\", and believed it to be her most \"refreshing\" offering since her work on ''[[Impossible Princess]]'' (1997).<ref>{{cite web|author=Nofli, Joey|url=http://ew.com/music/2018/01/19/kylie-minogue-dancing-new-song/|title=Kylie Minogue releases country-pop banger 'Dancing'|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> Sam Damshenas at ''[[Gay Times]]'' agreed, calling it a \"country-pop banger\" that may \"becom[e] a future Kylie classic\".<ref name=\"Damshenas\">{{cite web|author=Damshenas, Sam|url=http://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/97237/shes-back-listen-kylie-minogues-fantastic-comeback-single-dancing/|title=She's back! Listen to Kylie Minogue's fantastic comeback single Dancing|work=[[Gay Times]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> Matt Bagwell, writing for ''[[The Huffington Post]]'', wrote an article defining 10 moments of Kylie's career where she \"redefined pop music\", and listed ''Golden'' and \"Dancing\" as one of them; he called it her most \"surprising\" material yet, and praised the songwriting for being more \"in-depth\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Bagwell, Matt|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/kylie-minogue-new-single-album-dancing-golden-video_uk_5a61e85be4b01d91b254d3a1|title=From Hot Pants To Hoedowns... 10 Times Kylie Minogue Redefined Pop Music|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> Daniel Kreps from ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' described it as \"euphoric\", whereas [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] writer Mike Wass called it a \"cute country-pop hybrid with an instantly hummable chorus.\"<ref name=\"rollingstone\"/><ref>{{cite web|author=Wass, Mike|url=http://www.idolator.com/7673739/kylie-minogue-new-single-dancing|title=Kylie Minogue Teases Country-Pop Hybrid \"Dancing\" (Out Friday)|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=15 January 2018|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> Hannah J. Davis from ''[[The Guardian (UK)|The Guardian]]'' listed it as their \"Track of the Week\", declaring it as \"Raw yet danceable,\". She compared it to \"[[Dancing on My Own]]\" by Swedish singer [[Robyn]], believing it to be \"one of those songs that's a total bop but which, after a couple of merlots, might push you into the foetal position.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=J. Davis, Hannah|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/jan/26/kylie-minogue-dancing-track-of-week|title=Tracks of the week reviewed: Kylie, Young Thug and Bleachers|work=[[The Guardian (UK)|The Guardian]]|date=26 January 2018|accessdate=27 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nDescribed a lot \"mellower\" than her previous music, ''[[Express.co.uk]]'' contributor Shaun Kitchener believed it was \"still unmistakably Kylie\" by its production, and believed its chorus would \"satisfy her loyal fan base\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Kitchener, Shaun|url=https://www.express.co.uk/entertainment/music/906856/Kylie-Minogue-new-song-Dancing-Golden-album-listen-stream-comeback|title=Kylie Minogue COMEBACK: Listen to first single Dancing from new album|publisher=[[Express.co.uk]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=27 January 2018}}</ref> Although Similarly, [[MuuMuse]]'s Bradley Stern acknowledged that it wasn't what was \"expected\", but concluded that \"Dancing\" is a \"perfectly fine first step into this bold new era, and an assurance that she's going to keep doing what she does best until the very last shimmy,\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Stern, Bradley|url=https://muumuse.com/2018/01/kylie-minogue-dancing-review.html/|title=Kylie Minogue's \"Dancing\" Is a Twangy Midlife Ode to Mortality|publisher=[[MuuMuse]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=27 January 2018}}</ref> Cameron Adams from ''[[The Northern Star]]'' believed the track's sound would \"divide\" fans, but also compared its appeal to the work of ''Impossible Princess''\u2014which made a similar impact. Nevertheless, Adams said that \"Dancing\" is a \"smart first single as it is one of the most traditional Kylie moments on ''Golden''.\"<ref name=\"northenstar\">{{cite web|author=Adams, Cameron|url=https://www.northernstar.com.au/news/first-review-kylies-new-single-dancing-is-country-/3313759/|title=First review: Kylie's country club|work=[[The Northern Star]]|date=19 January 2018|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nUpon the release of ''Golden'', \"Dancing\" was selected as one of the album's highlights. Tim Sendra from [[AllMusic]] chose it as a standout track, and praised Minogue's ability to pull of both contemporary pop and country music.<ref>{{cite web|author=Sendra, Tim|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/golden-mw0003145096|title=Kylie Minogue - Golden|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|date=5 April 2018|accessdate=19 April 2018}}</ref> Ian Gormely from ''[[Exclaim!]]'' shared a similar opinion, stating that it \"is a great addition to the Kylie singles arsenal of earworms,\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Ian Gormely|url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/kylie_minogue-golden|title=Kylie Minogue: Golden Album Review|work=[[Exclaim!]]|date=5 April 2018|accessdate=19 April 2018}}</ref> ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' editor Ben Cardew opined that tracks like \"Dancing\" stay true to Minogue's dance-pop style, and described it as \"genuine brilliance.\" Moreover, he complimented the track's \"funny one-liner chorus... that perfectly sums up the way a great pop song can defy mortality.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Cardew, Ben|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/kylie-minogue-golden/|title=Kylie Minogue: Golden Album Review|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=5 April 2018|accessdate=19 April 2018}}</ref> Mark Kennedy at ''[[The Washington Post]]'' also commended her songwriting abilities, and described it as \"[[Dolly Parton]]-ish\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Kennedy, Mark|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/music/review-kylie-minogue-puts-on-cowboy-boots-for-a-country-cd/2018/04/04/a5688562-3810-11e8-af3c-2123715f78df_story.html|title=Review: Kylie Minogue puts on cowboy boots for a country CD|work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=4 April 2018|accessdate=19 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n\"Dancing\" made its official charting debut in New Zealand, opening at number seven on their regional [[Official New Zealand Music Chart|Heatseeker Singles Chart]]. This became the singer's first single to chart in the region since 2012's \"[[Timebomb (Kylie Minogue song)|Timebomb]]\", which reached number 33 on the country's top 40 chart.<ref name=\"nzchart\">{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=4447|title=NZ Heatseeker Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=29 January 2018|accessdate=26 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://charts.nz/showitem.asp?interpret=Kylie+Minogue&titel=Timebomb&cat=s|title=Kylie Minogue \u2013 Timebomb|publisher=Hung Median. charts.nz|date=4 June 2012|accessdate=27 January 2018}}</ref> In Minogue's native Australia, the song opening at number 46, tying with \"[[Into the Blue (Kylie Minogue song)|Into the Blue]]\" as her lowest-charting lead single in the country. Furthermore, it also reached number eight on the region's dance chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Kylie+Minogue&titel=Into+The+Blue&cat=s|title=Kylie Minogue \u2013 Into the Blue|publisher=Hung Median. Australian-Charts.com|date=16 February 2014|accessdate=6 February 2018}}</ref> Despite the single's low charting, \"Dancing\" received a gold certification denoting shipments of 35,000 units.<ref name=\"aria_cert\" /> In the United Kingdom, \"Dancing\" opened at number 47 on the [[UK Singles Chart]] before immediately dropping off, her first single to chart there since 2015's \"[[Only You (Yazoo song)|Only You]]\" with British comedian [[James Corden]].<ref name=\"ukchart\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/151212cluk.txt|title=Only You|publisher=Zobbel|accessdate=10 March 2018}}</ref> Once the video was released it re-entered at number 93 before leaving again for two weeks.<ref name=\"ukchart\"/> After her performance of the song on live television, the song re-entered at number 50, staying in the chart for another week after at number 61.<ref name=\"ukchart\"/> It later peaked at number 38 after the release of ''Golden'', becoming her fifty-first top 40 hit.<ref name=\"ukchart\"/> Moreover, it debuted at number five on the UK Indie Chart, number one on the Vinyl Singles chart, and peaked at number 10 on the [[Scottish Singles and Albums Charts|Scottish Singles Chart]].<ref name=\"ukdownloads\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-downloads-chart/|title=Official Singles Download Chart Top 100|publisher=The Official Chart Company|date=27 January 2018|accessdate=27 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"ukindie\"/><ref name=\"scottishchart\"/>\n\nIn Belgium, it entered the Wallonia [[Ultratip]] chart at number 46, and peaked at number 14 five weeks later.<ref name=\"Wallonia\"/> Additionally, it charted on the Flanders Ultratip chart at number 44, its final peak.<ref name=\"Flanders\"/> It also reached number five on the Digital Songs Chart in both Finland and Sweden, provided by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''.<ref name=\"Finland\"/> Due to live promotion of the single in Germany, it managed to enter their [[GfK Entertainment Charts|singles chart]] at number 98, Minogue's first appearance on the chart since \"Into the Blue\". The song later peaked at number 71.<ref name=\"GermanChart\"/> Additionally, \"Dancing\" made appearances on several radio charts throughout Europe, including in Hungary at number 17, and at number 19 in Poland.<ref name=\"Hungary\"/><ref name=\"Poland\"/> In the United States, the single made its debut on the [[Dance Club Songs]] at number 53. After 11 weeks, it rose to number one, becoming the singer's 14th song to top that chart.<ref name=\"DanceClubSongs\"/>\n\n==Music video==\nMinogue uploaded the official audio of \"Dancing\" on her [[YouTube]] channel on the same date of its release. The audio-only video features the single's artwork, consisting of her wearing a cowgirl outfit and leaning back while sitting in front of a stage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1Ei-P-v-O2M|title=Kylie Minogue - Dancing (Official Audio)|publisher=Minogue's [[YouTube]] channel|date=19 January 2015|accessdate=19 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe video for \"Dancing\" premiered on 1 February, following a backstage teaser confirming the date.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/kylieminogue/videos/10156249584650116/|title=Kylie Minogue|website=www.facebook.com}}</ref> Directed by [[Sophie Muller]], the country-inspired video was an homage to singers such as [[Dolly Parton]] as well as a return to Minogue's earlier choreography based videos. Minogue told ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', \"I always thought I could learn routines quickly, but this was different,\" she said. \"However, by the time I had to dance with the Grim Reaper at the end I had mastered it. And if that's not a funny allegory for life I don't know what is!\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/kylie-minogue-channels-dolly-parton-in-new-dancing-video-w516235|title=Watch Kylie Minogue Channel Dolly Parton in New 'Dancing' Video|work=Rolling Stone|date=1 February 2018|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Live performances==\nMinogue performed \"Dancing\" for the first time on ''[[Ant & Dec's Saturday Night Takeaway]]'' on 24 February 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2018-02-20/kylie-to-step-back-in-time-and-sing-her-greatest-hits-on-ant-decs-saturday-night-takeaway/|title=Kylie to step back in time and sing her greatest hits on Ant & Dec's Saturday Night Takeaway|publisher=Radio Times|date=20 February 2018|accessdate=23 February 2018}}</ref> The song was included on the setlist of [[Kylie Presents Golden]] concerts in March 2018. On 23 March, Minogue performed the song on [[Sport Relief]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/showbiz-news/kylie-minogue-sport-relief-manchester-14450106|title=Kylie Minogue mobbed by fans as she returns to Manchester for Sport Relief|work=Manchester Evening News|last=Houghton|date=23 March 2018|accessdate=23 March 2018}}</ref> On 12 April 2018, Minogue performed the song live during the German [[Echo Music Prize]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Schmidt|first=Axel|title=Skandal bei Echo 2018: Au\u00dfenminister Maas meldet sich zu Wort \u2013 Farid Bang in Schl\u00e4gerei verwickelt?|url=https://www.tz.de/stars/echo-2018-im-ticker-preistraeger-farid-bang-in-schlaegerei-verwickelt-zr-9774670.html|language=German|work=[[Tz (newspaper)|Tz]]|date=12 April 2018|accessdate=14 April 2018}}</ref> Minogue performed \"Dancing\" on the 25 April 2018 episode of ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]''; this was the song's debut performance for American television.<ref>{{cite web|last=Exposito|first=Suzy|title=Watch Kylie Minogue Flaunt Country Pop Hit 'Dancing' on 'Seth Meyers'|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/kylie-minogue-flaunts-new-country-pop-song-on-seth-meyers-w519580|website=Rolling Stone|date=26 April 2018|accessdate=27 April 2018}}</ref> Two days later, she performed the song on ''[[Good Morning America]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kylie Minogue performs on Good Morning America today|url=https://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/kylieminogue/view/175749/|website=Press Party|date=27 April 2018|accessdate=28 April 2018}}</ref> On 30 April 2018, Minogue performed the song on ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kylie Minogue Teaches Benedict Cumberbatch to Line Dance, Performs on 'Late Late Show': Watch|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8421024/kylie-minogue-late-late-show-performance-video|website=Billboard|date=1 May 2018|accessdate=2 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nMinogue performed \"Dancing\" as part of her set headlining [[Radio 2 Live in Hyde Park]]. She also closed her [[Golden Tour]] with \"Dancing\", where she wore a teal playsuit paired with grey embroidered thigh high boots.\n\n==Formats and track listings==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n*'''CD single / digital download'''<ref name=\"cdsingle\"/><ref name=\"goldendownload\"/>\n#\"Dancing\" \u2013 2:58\n\n*'''7\" vinyl'''<ref name=\"vinyl\"/>\n#\"Dancing\" \u2013 2:58\n#\"Rollin'\" \u2013 3:32\n\n*'''Digital download EP'''<ref name=\"websitedownload\"/>\n#\"Dancing\" \u2013 2:59\n#\"Dancing\" (Anton Powers edit) \u2013 3:04\n#\"Dancing\" (Illyus & Barrientos remix) \u2013 5:41\n#\"Dancing\" (Initial Talk remix) \u2013 3:44\n<!-- Don't add unsourced remixes here -->\n{{col-2}}\n*'''Digital download \u2013 Initial Talk remix'''<ref name=\"initial\">{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/dancing-initial-talk-remix-single/1351004219|title=Dancing (Initial Talk Remix)|publisher=iTunes UK|accessdate=26 January 2018}}</ref>\n#\"Dancing\" (Initial Talk remix) \u2013 3:43\n\n*'''Digital download \u2013 [[Illyus & Barrientos]] remix'''<ref name=\"illyus\">{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/dancing-illyus-barrientos-remix-single/1352950371|title=Dancing (Illyus & Barrientos remix) \u2013 Single|publisher=iTunes UK|accessdate=2 March 2018}}</ref>\n#\"Dancing\" (Illyus & Barrientos Remix) \u2013 5:41\n\n*'''Digital download \u2013 [[Anton Powers