oths<br />610\u2013687\u2013'''701/703'''</small>}}| boxstyle_Eg10=border-width:2px| Ci11=Cixilo| Pe11={{nowrap|[[Peter of Cantabria|Peter]]<br /><small>Duke of <br />Cantabria<br />?-730</small>}}}}\n{{chart|border=1| | | | | | | | | |,|-|-|-|+|-|-|-|.| | | |,|-|-|-|(| | | | | | | | | | | | | }}\n{{chart|border=1| | | | | | | | |Wi11 | |Op11 | |Si11 | |Al11 | |Fr11 | | | | | | | | | | | | | Wi11=[[Wittiza]]<br /><small>King of the<br />Visigoths<br />\u2248687\u2013'''694\u2013710'''?</small>| boxstyle_Wi11=border-width:2px| Op11=[[Oppas]]<br /><small>Bishop of Seville<br />?-712</small>| Si11=Sisebuto| Al11={{nowrap|[[Alfonso I of Asturias|Alfonso I]]<br /><small>King of Asturias<br />\u2248693-'''739\u2013757'''</small>}}| Fr11={{nowrap|[[Fruela of Cantabria|Fruela]]<br /><small>of Cantabria<br />?-758</small>}}}}\n{{chart|border=1| | | | | | | | | |!| | | | | | | | | | | |!| | | |!| | | | | | | | | | | | | }}\n{{chart|border=1| | | | | | | | |Ac12 | | | | | | | | | |KoA  | |KoA  | | | | | | | | | | | | | Ac12=<small>''?''</small><br />[[Achila II]]<br /><small>King of the<br />Visigoths<br />?-711\u2013714?</small>| boxstyle_Ac12=border-width:2px| KoA={{nowrap|[[List of Asturian monarchs|Kings of the]]<br />Kingdom of<br />[[Kingdom of Asturias|Asturias]]}}| boxstyle_KoA=border-width:0px; vertical-align:top}}\n{{chart/end}}\n{{chart bottom}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Spanish words of Germanic origin#Surnames|Spanish surnames of Goth origin]]\n*[[Romano-Germanic culture]]\n*For evidence of Visigothic taxation, see ''[[De fisco Barcinonensi]]''\n*[[Councils of Toledo]]\n*[[Germanic peoples]]\n*[[Arianism]]\n*[[Protofeudalism]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n{{refbegin}}\n\n*[[Bernard Bachrach|Bachrach, Bernard S.]] \"A Reassessment of Visigothic Jewish Policy, 589&ndash;711.\" ''American Historical Review'' 78, no. 1 (1973): 11&ndash;34.\n*Collins, Roger. ''The Arab Conquest of Spain, 710&ndash;797''. Oxford: Blackwell Publishers, 1989. Reprinted 1998